          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1683027743104-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>dried oregano</strong> to the pot with your <strong>chopped tomatoes</strong>, <strong>red wine vinegar</strong>,<strong> beef stock mix</strong>, <strong>tomato paste </strong>and<strong> </strong>450ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[650ml]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [850ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong> and stir it all together</p><p>Add <strong>half</strong> the <strong>chopped basil</strong> (save the rest for garnish!) with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and a very generous grind of <strong>black pepper</strong>, and bring to a boil over a high heat for 1 min, stirring until fully combined</p><p>Once boiling, roughly break your <strong>spaghetti </strong>in half, add it to the pot and mix it all together</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1683027752967-x200.jpg",
